tx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Monotheists%3A+Jews%2C+Christians%2C+and+Muslims+in+Conflict+and+Competition%2C+Volume+I%3A+The+Peoples+of+God&amp;rft.pages=88&amp;rft.pub=Princeton+University+Press&amp;rft.date=2005-07-25&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-691-12372-1&amp;rft.au=F.E.+Peters&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DRsafPfUjC6EC%26pg%3DPA88&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMuhammad" class="Z3988" about="#mwt887" id="mwBkw"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt887" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwBk0"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-170" id="cite_note-170"><a href="./Muhammad#cite_ref-170" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-170" class="mw-reference-text">Lewis (2002), p. 42</span></li><li about="#cite_note-171" id="cite_note-171"><a href="./Muhammad#cite_ref-171" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-171" class="mw-reference-text">Lings (1987), p. 255</span></li><li about="#cite_note-172" id="cite_note-172"><a href="./Muhammad#cite_ref-172" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-172" class="mw-reference-text">Vaglieri, <i id="mwBk4">Khaybar</i>, Encyclopedia of Islam</span></li><li about="#cite_note-King_Lings-173" id="cite_note-King_Lings-173"><span rel="mw:referencedBy"><a href="./Muhammad#cite_ref-King_Lings_173-0"><span class="mw-linkback-text">1 </span></a><a href="./Muhammad#cite_ref-King_Lings_173-1"><span class="mw-linkback-text">2 </span></a></span> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-King_Lings-173" class="mw-reference-text">Lings (1987), p. 260</span></li><li about="#cite_note-Kings_Khan-174" id="cite_note-Kings_Khan-174"><span rel="m