AM"><i id="mwCAQ">Islam: Its History, Teaching, and Practices</i></a>. <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Indiana" title="Indiana" id="mwCAU">Indiana</a>: <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Indiana_University_Press" title="Indiana University Press" id="mwCAY">Indiana University Press</a>. p.<span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwCAc"> </span>17. <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number" id="mwCAg">ISBN</a><span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwCAk"> </span><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Special:BookSources/978-0-253-21627-4" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-253-21627-4" id="mwCAo">978-0-253-21627-4</a>. <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20150924032200/https://books.google.com/books?id=my7hnALd_NkC&amp;pg=PA17#v=onepage&amp;q&amp;f=false" id="mwCAs">Archived</a> from the original on 24 September 2015.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Islam%3A+Its+History%2C+Teaching%2C+and+Practices&amp;rft.place=Indiana&amp;rft.pages=17&amp;rft.pub=Indiana+University+Press&amp;rft.date=2004&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-253-21627-4&amp;rft.aulast=Nigosian&amp;rft.aufirst=S.+A.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3Dmy7hnALd_NkC%26pg%3DPA17%23v%3Donepage%26q%26f%3Dfalse&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMuhammad" class="Z3988" about="#mwt1513" id="mwCAw"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt1513" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwCA0"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-267" id="cite_note-267"><a href="./Muhammad#cite_ref-267" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-267" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation encyclopaedia" about="#mwt1514" typeof="mw:Tra