Y8">Cornwell, Rupert (10 April 2015). <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/profiles/ayaan-hirsi-ali-islams-most-devastating-critic-10169031.html" id="mwCZA">"Ayaan Hirsi Ali: Islam's most devastating critic"</a>. <i id="mwCZE"><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./The_Independent" title="The Independent" id="mwCZI">The Independent</a></i>. <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./London" title="London" id="mwCZM">London</a><span class="reference-accessdate" id="mwCZQ">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap" id="mwCZU">26 September</span> 2017</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Independent&amp;rft.atitle=Ayaan+Hirsi+Ali%3A+Islam%27s+most+devastating+critic&amp;rft.date=2015-04-10&amp;rft.aulast=Cornwell&amp;rft.aufirst=Rupert&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.independent.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fpeople%2Fprofiles%2Fayaan-hirsi-ali-islams-most-devastating-critic-10169031.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMuhammad" class="Z3988" about="#mwt1912" id="mwCZY"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt1912" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwCZc"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-Warraq-325" id="cite_note-Warraq-325"><span rel="mw:referencedBy"><a href="./Muhammad#cite_ref-Warraq_325-0"><span class="mw-linkback-text">1 </span></a><a href="./Muhammad#cite_ref-Warraq_325-1"><span class="mw-linkback-text">2 </span></a></span> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-Warraq-325" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation book" about="#mwt1913" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite book ","href":"./Template:Cite_book"},"params":{"author":{"wt":"[[Ibn Warraq]]"},"date":{"wt":"2000"},"title":{"wt":"The Quest for the Historical Muhammad"},"